Gutach : even more security for pedestrians
they are not 100 metres apart : on Tuesday in Gutach the new B 33 pedestrian ampel was launched at the village park - within sight of the older town hall ampel .
two plants so close to each other : intent or thyroid ?
that question was clearly answered by Gutach &apos;s mayor yesterday .
&quot; the town hall floor was installed at the time because it secures the school path , &quot; Eckert explained yesterday .
the Kluser @-@ Ampel safe both cyclists and bus drivers and the Bergle residents .
the facility officially operational yesterday is important for the Sulzbachweg / Kirchstraße crushing area .
we have the museum , two churches , spa park , bus stop , doctor and bank as well as traffic flow from the residential area › Grub ‹ .
&quot; with the high traffic and pedestrian levels , another traffic light had to be their safety , &quot; Eckert said .
Peter Arnold also confirms this from Offenburg .
&quot; according to current measurements , on the B 33 daily about 12,000 vehicles pass through the community Gutach , of which about 10 percent are heavy duty , &quot; Arnold points out .
as a result , building another traffic light is more than necessary : &quot; security is just happening here , &quot; according to Arnold .
in total , four traffic views were carried out , and a roundabout was also considered , but due to the mess in the Sulzbachweg / Kirchstraße crushing area .
according to Arnold , everything was tested at the location of the Ampelmasten : &quot; by means of an extra transport for us with particularly long wooden trunks , we checked out whether these vehicles can drive out of the Sulzbachweg to the B 33 without cracking the traffic lights . &quot;
the approximately 15,000 @-@ euro traffic light system itself is the &quot; most modern thing there is currently on the market , &quot; Arnold explained .
the plant is equipped with coloured LEDs that shine so strongly that the lights can be seen by motorists , for example , even in deep sun .
and sparingly it is : the older light systems consume about 100 watts , the new just eight watts .
there are three light systems per ride .
Arnold explained the technology of the new plant : it is equipped with two radar sensors .
when the pedestrian hits the traffic light button , the upper radar sensor tests the traffic situation .
if the road is free , it comes immediately green for the pedestrian , if not , it takes about 15 seconds .
another radar sensor checks whether the green phase can be finished for pedestrians .
&quot; should a group or disabled people go across the street , the green phase will be extended , so everyone will surely come across the runway , &quot; Arnold explained .
of course , the motorist must think here as a partner and watch the runway .
this was not the case yesterday : barely showed the traffic lights for pedestrians green , smoked an upper class vehicle - in bright red .
