the disasters of his Catholic villain - the faintness , the slope to raw violence and blunt sexuality , the duck and freudlessness - has often been described by the Carinthian poet .
the prize winner is known mainly as a prosawriter , theatre texts are in his work .
Collage from Prosatexten Gerhard Fresacher presents for his performance &quot; Weather lights on the guild tip , &quot; which can now be seen in garage X at Petersplatz , a collage made of prosatexten .
the theatre designer combines elements of the autobiographical novel &quot; The Leibeigene &quot; ( 1987 ) with saminizes from &quot; Leichnam , his family belauernd &quot; ( 2003 ) .
on the largely empty stage - important props : a cordoned sofa , on which to copy and masturbate - the eight @-@ member ensemble hanged through the text material .
in doing so , director Fresacher seems to have little faith in the text .
the 70 @-@ minute performance outpaced the template with a plethora of regimen , known from the repertoire of post @-@ dramatic play forms .
the actresses , in particular , come across the sometimes somewhat questionable scenic changes .
they are grabbed hard , with their head dipped under water , with their evening robes chopped to the wall .
forced into Zellophan or tenant , they staked on dangerously high sticks by staging , either monologizing them loudly or lying completely silent on the stage floor .
however , the text is hardly conveyed in this way .
