us border : &apos; super tunnel &apos; to drug smuggling discovered
at the border between Mexico and the US , investigators have discovered and shut down a &quot; super @-@ tunnel &quot; to drug smuggling .
as the US customs authorities reported , the more than 500 @-@ metre tube between Tijuana and San Diego was equipped with electricity , rail tracks and a ventilation system .
three suspects were thus arrested , eight tonnes of marijuana and nearly 150 kilograms of cocaine seized .
according to the data , the tunnel had not yet been used .
&quot; these cartels are stupid if they think they could dig themselves under the radar , &quot; the Attorney General of the U.S. District of Southern California , Laura Duffy , said at a news conference in front of a warehouse in San Diego , where that had discovered an end to the tunnel .
contacted the drug gangs , Duffy asserted : &quot; if you continue to build such tunnels and try to use them , we are determined to make this a huge waste of dirty money . &quot;
both the U.S. authorities and Mexican security forces are in a permanent fight against drug cartels .
more than 7,000 people have been killed in Mexico since 2006 in connection with drug crime .
constructed by experts
because of the tunnel &apos;s elaborate equipment , investigators assume it was constructed by architects and engineers and that construction took place around a year .
the track system was so equipped that electric cars could be used there .
on the Mexican side , access lies in a building 80 metres from the border .
according to authorities , a ladder leads 20 metres into depth to the actual tunnel entrance .
the tunnel has a cross @-@ section of 1.20 metres height and 90 inches width .
it would also have been appropriate to promote illegal immigration towards the US .
two of the suspects have been arrested in connection with the cocaine fund .
the third , a Mexican , was captured because of the seized marijuana .
all three face a maximum sentence of life imprisonment , officials said .
eight such tunnels have been discovered since 2006 , the San Diego press conference said .
however , it is the first time that cocaine has been found in such tunnel construction .
normally , cocaine is smuggled in smaller quantities rather than tunnels .
this shows the &quot; despair &quot; of drug gangs whose traditional routes have since been cut off , said Bill Sherman of the drug investigation DEA in San Diego .
they would do all they can to enter the US .
no details were announced on the arrests , at least one was Mexicans , it said .
you have to face prison sentences of up to 10 years .
