Frontier Airlines charges for hand luggage
Frontier Airlines plans to charge up to $ 100 from passengers who want to dump hand luggage on their flight .
Frontier Airlines intends to charge up to $ 100 for a piece of hand baggage and $ 2 for coffee or lemonade , even if in the announcement on Wednesday to read that passengers should keep the whole can .
the new fee applies to hand baggage in the baggage box above the seat , small bags under the seat remain free of charge .
Frontier explained that you calculate $ 25 if the fee is paid in advance , and $ 100 for travelers who paid only at the flight &apos;s height .
frontier spokeswoman Kate O &apos;Malley said the fee of $ 100 aims to encourage travelers to take care of the payment in advance .
&quot; we don &apos;t want to calculate that amount , &quot; she explained .
airlines began charging for the first and second items of luggage in 2008 .
passengers who tried to bypass them have therefore stamped as much as possible into the hand baggage , which means that the luggage bags are often overcrowded over the seat .
fees are one way to encourage passengers to take less on board .
O &apos;Malley said that at the new fee , it &apos;s not really about making money .
it &apos;s about Frontier &apos;s most loyal customers , who would have clearly expressed that it &apos;s getting harder to find space in the compartment above the seat .
passengers who buy your tickets on the airline &apos;s website do not have to pay .
this means that a passenger at Frontier &apos;s airstrip may be allowed to take a piece of baggage free of charge , but the next person will have to pay $ 100 for a similar piece of baggage .
O &apos;Malley explained that Frontier &apos;s website and check @-@ in procedures would be changed so passengers would be informed about the fee before they would go to the airstrip .
Frontier &apos;s new hand baggage charge will enter into force only in the summer , a precise date is not yet available .
passengers often flick over baggage charges and other charges , but airlines like to resort to it .
they argue that transporting the baggage should cost money and passengers should pay that service if they wanted it .
many on Wall Street view the new baggage charges as a sign that airlines are taking enough money to cover the cost of air travel after years of losses .
however , most leave the fingers of charges for hand luggage so far .
spirit Airlines Inc. demanded three years ago as the first charge for hand baggage and later followed Allegiant Air , also a convenience store .
the only other airline with such a fee is the Hungarian Wizz Air , said airline consultant Jay Sorensen , who is closely monitoring the additional charges .
he estimated in a December 2011 report that the hand baggage charge Spirit is $ 50 million a year .
Sorensen , who previously held a leadership position at Midwest Airlines , has recently flown with Spirit and was curious about what would expect him at the airstrip if passengers were confronted with the company &apos;s unusual hand baggage charge .
&quot; the boarding process was among the most smooth I experienced in my career in aviation , &quot; he said .
I expected to see teeth and tangible discussions at the airstrip .
&quot; the plane was full , &quot; he explained , &quot; and the boarding ran like shuttered . &quot;
Frontier also follows Spirit at the $ 2 required for coffee , tea , lemonade or juice .
the company explained that passengers who bought lemonade or juice should keep the whole can and add coffee for free .
water remains free .
us Airways had been short @-@ lived in 2008 trying to demand money for soft drinks , but reversed it seven months later after passengers complained and no other major company was trailing .
frontrunner step to charge for hand baggage if passengers don &apos;t buy directly at the airline is the latest initiative to steer customers to their own website .
airlines pay online travel agencies such as orbitz 10 to 25 US dollars per ticket sold .
this gives all companies an incentive to move passengers to direct purchase at them rather than via an online travel agency .
however , Frontier has gone the furthest in this area .
in September , the company began to award only half as many frequent flyer miles when booking through an online travel agency .
on Wednesday , miles were cut again to 25 per cent of the flight route .
a flight flight booked at a third party with Frontier over 1000 miles will therefore only bring customers 250 miles .
passengers can also reserve seats only at direct purchase on Frontier &apos;s website .
Frontier has a loyal customer base at its headquarters in Denver , but the business is shrinking and the company is losing money .
the proceeds fell 9 per cent and flight capacity shrank just 13 per cent in the first quarter , as read in the financial report released Wednesday by the parent company , Republic Airways Holdings Inc .
Republic has tried to control Frontier &apos;s finances as part of the sale of the Company .
