many businesses have responded to attitudes so far .
one reason for this is according to the fields farmer : &quot; we have few skilled workers in the craft industry , healthcare and care for the elderly . &quot;
since September , employment opportunities for staff in the hotel and restaurant industry have been running again .
the winter season begins in mid @-@ December .
the full background report can be found in the Allgäuer Scoreboard from 31.10.2013 ( page 33 ) .
profit plunge at Bombardier after drop in delivery numbers and orders
Canadian aircraft and rail manufacturer Bombardier Inc reported a 15 per cent drop in net profit on Thursday after being pressured by declining orders and deliveries on aircraft in the third quarter as well as contract problems in the rail sector .
Bombardier , based in Montreal , also released no flight test data for its brand new CSeries aircraft and did not provide any new information on whether the aircraft could go into commercial use in accordance with the ambitious timetable next September .
only three more starts have been followed by the maiden flight of the test aircraft one and a half months ago , which makes it questionable whether the test phase will take place as planned .
the results fell short of forecasts , leading to a fall of more than eight percent on the Toronto Stock Exchange .
Cameron Doerksen , analyst at National Bank Financial , on Thursday cut his valuation of &quot; outperform &quot; on &quot; sector performance &quot; in view of the stock &apos;s limited price potential over the next one to two quarters .
&quot; while weaker delivery numbers on aircraft were expected as much as possible , we are clearly disappointed by the margin development in the transport sector , &quot; Doerksen said in a customer letter .
we believe Bombardier will receive new orders for the CSeries when the test program for the aircraft progresses .
however , if no new orders are announced in the coming months , we expect the market to become more sceptical about the programme .
Bombardier hopes the CSeries aircraft will catapult the company into the lower market segment currently dominated by Boeing and Airbus .
the first test plane was presented to the public in March and flew to the public for the first time in September after months of delays .
but so far binding orders for the CSeries are moderate with 177 as potential buyers wait for the results of the flight tests and want to see whether the company &apos;s claims regarding fuel efficiency and cost @-@ saving potential of the new jet transport aircraft are accurate .
there are currently a total of 403 orders and commitments from 15 customers and companies .
chief executive Pierre Beaudoin is confident that Bombardier will reach its target of 300 binding orders at the start of commercial use of the jet .
the company &apos;s management also assured analysts and media on Thursday that the program is in the schedule .
&quot; the test plane is no longer on the ground than expected , &quot; Beaudoin said at a conference call and added that during the plane &apos;s standoff , ground tests and software updates were scheduled .
each manufacturer plans differently .
we decided to take a first flight and then mount an overprocessing period , which we did .
this is happening throughout the flight programme .
the second of five test aircraft is expected to start in the next few weeks , the remaining one shortly after , it said from the company side .
still , analysts remain skeptical about whether 12 months after the maiden flight , the first customer can launch a CSeries plane .
Bombardier said it is reviewing planning for commissioning ( EIS ) and will update it in the next few months .
&quot; the slow progress of the flight test - even if they obviously correspond to BOMBARDIERS internal planning - reinforces our view that commissioning is shifting to the first quarter of 2015 , &quot; Doerksen said .
in the third quarter ended September 30 , BOMBARDIERS net profit fell to $ 147 million , or 8 cents per share , from $ 172 million , or 9 cents per share , the year before .
adjusted earnings per share are unchanged 9 cents .
sales dropped slightly , falling from 4.2 to $ 4.1 billion .
analysts had expected a gain of 10 cents per share and sales of $ 4.56 billion , according to Thomson Reuters I / B / E / S.
the world &apos;s fourth @-@ largest aircraft maker announces it has delivered 45 aircraft this quarter , a drop of 57 last year .
net orders fell from 83 aircraft to 26 .
the order book in the aerospace sector was $ 32.9 billion on September 30 , unchanged from December 31 .
&quot; in the aerospace sector , the results were within our specifications , but the low order intake and market conditions overall were disappointing , &quot; Beaudoin said .
sales in the aerospace sector fell 13 percent to $ 2 billion .
Bombardier , the world &apos;s largest rail manufacturer , announced that sales in this division have risen by just 11 per cent to $ 2.1 billion .
the order book in the transport sector was $ 32.6 billion on September 30 , slightly increased from December 31 .
the profit margin in the transport sector has been affected by resolution problems in some large contracts .
according to management , there will be new guidance for the fourth quarter .
in afternoon trading Thursday , the Bombardier stock shed 8.5 per cent and was at 4.83 Canadian dollars after also announced that Google &apos;s chief financial officer Patrick Pichette will switch to the board .
Brazilian Embraer SA , the world &apos;s third @-@ largest commercial aircraft maker and BOMBARDIERS closest rival , reported a 10 percent drop in quarterly profit on Thursday .
