for example , the 2015 elections to the parish council will change the basic spirit of Haslach ( SE ) .
there is only one common parish council for all six parishes .
in a joint meeting on Saturday , the bodies of Haslach , Hofstetten , Mühlenbach , Fischbach , Steinach and Welschensteinach were preparing for the changes .
there is nothing to change in the basic decisions of the diocese and it is up to the parish communities to implement them as satisfactorily as possible .
during the day , it became particularly clear : skepticism about the New softer but more tense to confidence .
from the ideas and expectations of the changes in 2015 to concrete proposals on the future composition and size of the parish council , the extremely constructive discussions of the six bodies with the full official members of the peace team ranged .
on the basis of a presentation , regional dekan Georg Schmitt explained the new guidelines for the conservation units in the Archdiocese of Freiburg .
after that , the SE Haslach , as a parish , will form a body of public law that will enter the rights and duties of the six different church communities .
there will only be a common parish council and a council of trustees representing the parish authority .
at least two elected members will be represented from each parish , and the six parish teams will be formed on the ground .
their task will be to promote church life in the place in the future .
when it came to the question of the finances of each parish , there was considerable need for dialogue .
the new rules provide for the allocation of funds in the parish .
the liabilities , on the other hand , go to the entire community .
