the main reason for the forthcoming price increase is the increase in the so @-@ called EEG levy from 5,277 to 6,3 cents per kilowatt hour .
this levy will be reset each year in October by the four operators of the major power lines .
these quantify the additional costs arising from the energy change that they can charge through a levy on the electricity price .
the towns of Pfullendorf form the last link in this chain .
in its forecasts , the Energy Company &apos;s Supervisory Board even assumed a higher levy , as Jörg @-@ Arne Bias reports .
now the actual figures would have to be calculated before the city works could inform their customers of the exact price increase next week .
&quot; we &apos;re going from an increase of 1 cent plus x , &quot; Bias said , with the figure more likely to be near the 2 cents .
traffic light on permanent red : watch waiting time
sometimes a traffic light just doesn &apos;t get green .
contact lines in the street do not respond , or the light sign is defective .
what should you do - go to Red ?
if a person has waited long enough at a red traffic light and the crossing is free , he can continue , explains Ralf Becker in the magazine &quot; Motorrad . &quot;
however , the waiting period must be &apos; appropriate &apos; , which could be interpreted differently from one case to another .
Becker advises you to run at least five minutes before starting a function disturbance of the traffic light .
however , anyone who continues to drive despite red light must be aware that he is fully responsible for an accident caused by it .
anyone who tolerates less than five minutes may not wait long enough , warns Becker and points to a decision by the High Court of Hamm .
in the negotiated case , a driver had ignored the traffic light after about three minutes of continuous red and had to answer for a negligent red light offense .
after all , the traffic light was not defective , but jumped on green soon .
he was spared a driving ban because of the particular situation - but the fine did not .
