Vienna airport creates passenger calls
Mr Max Maier , please come to Gate 24 .
it will no longer be possible to tell how this will happen at Vienna @-@ Schwechat Airport .
much of the loudspeaker passes away - the noise level should be reduced so much .
creating a more relaxed atmosphere is the aim of this innovation .
as Airport spokesman Peter Kleemann announced to Radio Vienna , Vienna Airport is following an international trend with the cessation of passes affecting individuals .
for example , airports in Copenhagen , Frankfurt or Dubai are already abandoning noisy calls .
by dropping these passes - on average , around 200 personal calls by loudspeakers on a day - it is expected to be quiet at the airport in the future .
&quot; it has also become apparent in the experience that these individual passes have been relatively little noticed , but at the same time all other information about changed flight levels or departures here has been underperformed a bit , &quot; Kleemann said in conversation with the radio station .
