fighting : no absolute protection possible
&quot; we want to involve residents early in planning , &quot; Mayor Jens Houter opened the Citizens &apos; Information Conference on the flood protection concept in Gechingen .
about 80 participants had come to the municipal hall to explain the measures planned , ask questions , raise concerns and bring ideas .
Houter made it clear : &quot; the eventual decisions take the members of the council . &quot;
the flooding , which hit Gechingen on May 15 , 2009 , unprepared , was a cutting @-@ edge event that raised questions about protections for the future , according to Houter .
a river basin investigation had been commissioned with the neighbouring community of Aidlingen , which is now the basis for the flood protection concept in Gechingen .
&quot; the protection of as many plots as possible is the goal , &quot; says Houter .
the planning of protection against flooding , according to the German weather service , is based on statistics every 100 years .
climate change is taken into account by a 15 % surcharge .
this is called &quot; HQ 100aClimate . &quot;
the water masses , which had caused significant damage in 2009 , matched a 1,000 @-@ year flooding .
&quot; there is no absolute protection , but a relative improvement we can achieve , &quot; Houter added .
in order to secure the protection of HQ 100aclimate , around four million euros will have to be invested in fighting , with the community expected to face national subsidies of around 70 per cent .
Houter pointed out , however , that there is support only if an overall approach is implemented .
to this end , the community needs the participation of its citizens .
a complex planning and authorisation procedure must be completed .
it is best to start implementation in 2016 .
among other things , the concept of protection , which was presented in the local council last week ( we reported ) , provides for local measures in the flow of the river Irm from the National Valley .
following the presentation of the flood protection concept , participants took the opportunity to contribute their concerns .
among other things , it questioned why no more dams and reservoirs were planned to protect the place .
Gregor Kühn , specialist planner of the commissioned engineering firm Wald and Corbe from Hügelsheim , who presented the concept , stressed that it needed the interaction of all the measures presented to achieve the desired goal in the sum .
in addition , you can find the most economical solution , according to Joachim Forest of Forest and Corbe .
resentment prevailed among residents of the old town who , even with normal thunderstorms , have repeatedly suffered from overload of the canal network .
the problem is well @-@ known with administration and initial measures have already been taken .
however , Houter pointed out that the guidelines for canal systems are different than for flood protection and should not be mixed .
the community is required to interpret the canal network in such a way that two @-@ to @-@ three @-@ year regenerals could be entangled .
making sewage channels larger would spare millions .
