parents of a teenager from Georgia who died in tragic accident believe in murder
the teenager &apos;s parents , whose body was found in a collapsed ridge in the gym of his high school , are convinced her son was murdered , the family &apos;s lawyer said Thursday .
Kendrick Johnson from Valdosta in the U.S. state of Georgia was found on January 11 in an upright mat standing behind the grandstand in the school turntable .
the sheriff &apos;s investigative officers from Lowndes County concluded that Johnson died in a tragic accident , but that the 17 @-@ year @-@ old &apos;s family was doubtful .
&quot; they are convinced that their son was murdered , &quot; Benjamin Crump , the lawyer for Kenneth and Jacquelyn Johnson , told FoxNews.com.
they would never have believed he had died as the sheriff concluded .
&quot; they believe that there is no logic whatsoever against the laws of physics as well as against common sense , &quot; Crump .
rather , they are convinced the truth will be covered to protect the person or persons responsible for their son &apos;s death .
&quot; her son went to school for learning and came back in the body bag , &quot; he commented .
U.S. Attorney Michael Moore said Thursday that there will be a formal investigation into Johnson &apos;s death as a number of important issues remain unresolved .
what was the cause of death ?
is his death due to a crime ?
that &apos;s what Moore said at a news conference Thursday afternoon .
I follow the facts in whatever direction they take .
my aim is to find out the truth .
&quot; I take the view that there is a sufficient basis for a formal investigation , &quot; he said .
Moore told reporters the initial autopsy indicated that Johnson had died of the consequences of an &quot; opposition @-@ related suffocation . &quot;
a second autopsy , however , caused another cause of death , according to Moore .
&quot; there are a number of questions that need to be answered or confirmed , &quot; he said .
