the project is a key element in the energy security of the entire European continent .
South Stream is expected to provide more diversity in Russia &apos;s export routes through Europe .
a contract dispute between Gazprom and its counterparts in Ukraine , where most of Russia &apos;s gas is stored for Europe , provides for increased risk in conventional routes , as is heard by the official .
Miller said the direct link to Bulgaria , a member of the European Union , meant that geopolitical risks associated with transit countries were &quot; forever &quot; switched off .
Bulgarian consumers get gas from South Stream at discounted fares when the entire project enters into operation in 2015 .
according to Gazprom , construction work in other subordinated countries is expected to begin on the planned route towards the end of the year .
the pipeline is designed for an annual capacity of 62.3 billion cubic feet of natural gas .
