Pope Francis appoints first cardinals in February
Pope Francis will first convene new cardinals of the Catholic Church on February 22 , as the Vatican announced Thursday .
Cardinals are the most senior clerics in the Catholic Church after the Pope and they are also who choose a pope , so Francis will appoint the first group of men who will ultimately participate in the election of his successor .
there are currently 201 cardinals .
however , a cardinal who has reached an age of 80 can no longer participate in the papal election - that falls to a group of 120 &quot; eligible cardinals . &quot;
in a statement announcing the news , Father Federico Lombardi , a spokesman for the Vatican , said there will be a meeting of all cardinals before the ceremony is held to appoint the new cardinals , which is also known as Consistorium .
&quot; Pope Francis decided to announce his decision to convene the Consensus in February in advance so that other meetings that require the participation of cardinals from around the world can be planned , &quot; Lombardi said .
Jack Valero of Catholic Voices said the number of eligible cardinals will likely have fallen by February .
he explained that a pope normally recounts as many cardinals as necessary so that the number of eligible cardinals again looks at 120 , and as many cardinals over 80 as he would like .
the consistency next year is significant because it is the first since the election of Francis in March this year , according to Valero .
there is currently a certain overhang on the part of Europe and , in particular , Italy .
&quot; it will be interesting to see if the new Pope will appoint cardinals from the rest of the world to restore balance , &quot; he said .
forty percent of Catholics live in South America , but they have only a tiny number of cardinals .
the Cardinals will also be the first to be called since the formation of the council of cardinals founded by Francis , a group of eight cardinals from around the world who have the task of finding ways to reform the church .
in the past , the pope decided everything alone .
&quot; now Francis has chosen these eight cardinals to help him , &quot; Valero said .
he explained that it was &quot; well possible &quot; that Francis would ask the Cardinals for advice .
but so far we have not been in this position - all this is completely new .
Valero said that typically the bishops would be called to cardinals from large places , but stole Francis &quot; full of surprises - so we don &apos;t know who he is appointing . &quot;
GM calls for new pickup truck in the US to repair seating
general Motors is calling for nearly 19,000 of its brand @-@ new Chevrolet Silverado and GMC Sierra @-@ Pickup Trucks with construction year 2014 to fix a problem with the manually adjustable seat residue , according to a statement from the U.S. regulator for vehicle safety on Friday .
for some of the cars , there can be a defect in the mechanism for setting back the front seat residue .
for this reason , they do not comply with the federal guidelines on vehicle safety at head bases .
&quot; if you drive from behind on the vehicle , it is possible that head support does not properly protect inmates , so there is an increased risk of injury , &quot; was read in the news on the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration &apos;s website ( NHTSA ) .
the recalled models were manufactured between 1 August and 10 September .
delivery of the GM Trucks began in June and represents the main model launch of the leading U.S. automaker since the 2009 insolvent restructuring .
GM informed vehicle owners in the first half of October about the defect .
NHTSA could not check the notification letter because of the 16 @-@ day government shutdown , which had a negative impact on car sales in October .
the sale of the Silverado and Sierra Trucks , which were redeveloped for the 2014 model year , has risen 20 percent in the first 10 months of the year , GM said Friday .
