with five to four votes , the judges ruled that the individual mandate of the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act - forcing U.S. citizens to complete health insurance or pay a penalty by 2014 - is unconstitutional under the state &apos;s tax authority .
top Justice John Roberts hit the side of the four more liberal members of the chamber , while judges Scalia , Thomas , Alito and Kennedy decided against it .
the Court also confirmed the remaining sections of the 2700 pages of the law and also considered that the provision of the health law requiring states to either extend the conditions for access to Medicaid or otherwise remove all state Medicaid subsidies is not unconstitutional .
